39 void normalizeSecNSec(uint32_t& sec, uint32_t& nsec)
40 {
41  uint32_t nsec_part = nsec % 1000000000UL;
42  uint32_t sec_part = nsec / 1000000000UL;
43  sec += sec_part;
44  nsec = nsec_part;
45 }
46 
47 Time& Time::fromNSec(int32_t t)
48 {
49  sec = t / 1000000000;
50  nsec = t % 1000000000;
51  normalizeSecNSec(sec, nsec);
52  return *this;
53 }
54 
55 Time& Time::operator +=(const Duration &rhs)
56 {
57  sec = sec - 1 + rhs.sec;
58  nsec = nsec + 1000000000UL + rhs.nsec;
59  normalizeSecNSec(sec, nsec);
60  return *this;
61 }
62 
63 Time& Time::operator -=(const Duration &rhs){
64  sec = sec - 1 - rhs.sec;
65  nsec = nsec + 1000000000UL - rhs.nsec;
66  normalizeSecNSec(sec, nsec);
67  return *this;
68 }
69 
70 Duration Time::operator-(const Time &rhs) const {
71  // Note: Considers wrap around as a continuation of time, e.g.,
72  // (0,0) - (0xFFFFFFFF, 0) = (1, 0)
73  Duration d;
74  d.sec = sec > rhs.sec ? sec - rhs.sec : -(rhs.sec - sec);
75  d.nsec = nsec > rhs.nsec ? nsec - rhs.nsec : -(rhs.nsec - nsec);
76  normalizeSecNSecSigned(d.sec, d.nsec);
77  return d;
78 }
79 }
